Three times someone that was Jesus' right-hand man.

27:44.696 --> 27:46.898
What does that look like in our today life?

27:49.026 --> 27:52.810
Maybe at work, we ask you, are you a Christian?

27:53.171 --> 27:54.532
Or can someone pray for us?

27:54.732 --> 27:59.277
And I don't want people to sing, but you know.

28:02.200 --> 28:02.441
No.

28:04.823 --> 28:11.370
Sometimes just that thing you say, just that stepping up is a difference someone needs.

28:13.313 --> 28:18.258
That truth that Jesus wants communicated in that situation,

28:18.882 --> 28:21.085
May just be the one thing that person needs.

28:25.812 --> 28:31.581
And in a words, he repented genuinely.

28:33.944 --> 28:46.162
And it was forgiving and eventually became a pillar, the rock on which the church was built.

28:50.338 --> 28:51.399
Why am I saying that?

28:52.220 --> 28:54.082
We ask ourselves to do, where are we?

28:54.102 --> 28:58.025
And you wonder, why am I repeating this?

28:58.726 --> 28:59.727
It is important.

29:01.148 --> 29:06.854
Have we been in a situation where we have denied Jesus in one way or the other?

29:08.956 --> 29:19.666
Have we been in a situation where we are supposed to advocate or supposed to preach or supposed to win someone or supposed to

29:20.034 --> 29:22.757
Communicate God's love to someone and we've held back.

29:25.920 --> 29:31.625
Remember, He is faithful and just to forgive us.

29:33.307 --> 29:34.208
He just repents.

29:37.011 --> 29:40.114
Let's thank God for our gifts, the gift of salvation.

29:45.219 --> 29:48.722
The gift that we all have by His grace,

29:53.314 --> 29:54.215
But then what?

29:56.719 --> 30:03.890
Let's think about how we can help others come to this gift.

30:07.736 --> 30:12.022
That's the whole point of my standing here today.

30:13.324 --> 30:17.010
That's the whole point of this bridge.

30:23.522 --> 30:23.963
Amen.

30:29.572 --> 30:30.193
Let us pray.

30:31.455 --> 30:32.396
Father, we thank you.

30:33.438 --> 30:34.379
We give you praise.

30:34.439 --> 30:35.401
We give you glory.

30:35.802 --> 30:36.503
We honor you.

30:36.523 --> 30:37.524
We thank you for your word.

30:38.326 --> 30:41.451
We thank you for your son dying for us.

30:42.593 --> 30:44.536
We thank you for the gift of salvation.

30:46.038 --> 30:51.026
Yes, we have declared with our mouth

30:53.122 --> 31:10.886
who've made that translation from the kingdom of darkness, the kingdom of your dear son, Lord Jesus, help us to not just receive this gift for ourselves only, for father, for you help us to do with it.

31:10.906 --> 31:22.802
As your son did, help us to go into our world, to communicate this to our world, it's not to be shy of communicating you to the world.

31:23.010 --> 31:25.213
in any way, shape, or form.

31:26.274 --> 31:30.299
Help us to receive grace to do that on a constant basis.

31:33.223 --> 31:38.169
Help us to be example of believers in our word, thoughts, and deeds.

31:39.250 --> 31:43.275
Help us to continue to confess Jesus as our Lord.

31:47.440 --> 31:48.882
Thank you, Jesus, for you.

31:52.258 --> 31:54.642
for the gift, your gift that you've given to us.

31:54.803 --> 31:55.644
We are grateful.

31:58.710 --> 31:59.050
Amen.

32:02.677 --> 32:04.160
We've come to the end of this week's message.

32:04.801 --> 32:06.444
We hope you've been impacted and inspired.

32:07.266 --> 32:14.098
